survey.music_making: I have been playing music since I was 11 years old. I performed in concert, symphonic, jazz, and marching band. From age 11 to 17, I learned and played clarinet, trumpet, and filled in for percussion. I've played the national anthem at Miller Park a few times. At age 16, I bought my first acoustic guitar and self-taught from then on. It is now my main instrument. I also bought a keyboard around the same time, which I was able to learn, but never got serious about. I still use, though, to teach my kids notes and melodies. Recently, I purchased an electric guitar and have been playing that as well. Music is and always will be a huge part of my life.
survey.activities: I listen to music almost everywhere I can. This includes driving, working out, doing chores, hanging out with my family/friends, while gardening, walking.
survey.habit_change: I remember a time when I used to be embarrassed to play the music I liked over speakers. Being judged by my music preferences is not something I ever think about now. I listen to all sorts of genres back to back.
survey.habits: I have a tendency to stick to one album for a few days if I like it. This only happens if I like the entire album, though, or if the songs go in some sort of story sequence. I like to decipher that for myself, too, which is why I sometimes repeat these albums. Once I am over an album, I go back to DJ stations, where there's a mix of what I've liked over time and new songs from artists I like or are similar to songs I've liked.
